<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,874]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,340,770,796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[355,448,770,795]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erici" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[355,448,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">A. erici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[462,536,770,796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[462,536,770,796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
belongs to a group of Neotropical species characterized by having the pronotum excavate in middle and elytra caudate. The pubescence, together with the form of the elytral apex, separates this species from all others.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
